# Adding a New Domain Entity

When adding a new entity (e.g., `Order`), create these files in order:

## 1. Domain Layer (`src/Domain/Orders/`)

- `Order.cs` — immutable `record` with all fields
- `Commands.cs` — `CreateOrderCommand`, `PatchOrderCommand` records
- `OrderRepository.cs` — `IOrderRepository` interface with async methods
- `OrderValidators.cs` — static validation methods
- `OrderService.cs` — orchestrates validators + repository + transactions

## 2. Infrastructure Layer (`src/Infrastructure/Orders/`)

- `OrderRepository.cs` — implements `IOrderRepository` using Dapper + `IDbContext`

## 3. API Layer (`src/Api/Orders/`)

- `OrderContracts.cs` — request/response records + FluentValidation validators
- `OrderEndpoints.cs` — `MapOrderEndpoints` extension method on `RouteGroupBuilder`

## 4. Wiring

- Register in `Program.cs`: `AddScoped<IOrderRepository, OrderRepository>()` and `AddScoped<OrderService>()`
- Map endpoints: `api.MapOrderEndpoints()`

## 5. Database

- Create migration: `make migrate-create NAME=create_orders_table`

## 6. Tests

- Add `tests/Domain.Tests/Orders/OrderValidatorsTests.cs`
